---
import "../styles/about.css";
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Samuel Reichert"
  description="Senior Frontend Engineer. React Native developer. Lover of travel, books, investing, and fitness."
  path="/about"
>

  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow reveal-eager">About</span>
      <h1 class="reveal-eager" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        A frontend engineer<br/>
        <span class="it">with a long-term thesis.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lede reveal-eager">
        I'm Samuel — a Senior Frontend Engineer based in Amsterdam. I build for the web,
        love what React Native is becoming, and treat every interface as a small piece of
        writing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-split">
        <figure class="portrait reveal" style="margin:0;">
          <div class="frame-corner fc-tl"></div>
          <div class="frame-corner fc-tr"></div>
          <div class="frame-corner fc-bl"></div>
          <div class="frame-corner fc-br"></div>
          <span class="monogram">SR</span>
          <div class="caption">— Samuel Reichert · MMXXVI —</div>
        </figure>

        <div class="about-text">
          <div class="reveal" style="--reveal-delay:80ms;">
            <span class="eyebrow">The work</span>
            <h2 style="margin-top:1rem;">
              Crafting interfaces that<br/>
              <span class="it">feel inevitable.</span>
            </h2>
            <p style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
              For over a decade I've shipped products in React, TypeScript and the
              half-dozen tools that orbit them. The titles changed — engineer, lead,
              senior — but the obsession didn't: how a screen feels when you reach for it,
              how typography breathes at every breakpoint, how a click can feel like a
              decision instead of a step.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top:1rem;">
              React Native pulled me back into the mobile world. There's something honest
              about a phone in the hand — no clever pointer states, no excuses. Just
              motion, weight, and intent.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="reveal" style="--reveal-delay:160ms;">
            <p class="pull">
              Good software, like good tailoring, hides its seams. The user shouldn't
              notice the work — only feel that they're in capable hands.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="reveal" style="--reveal-delay:200ms;">
            <span class="eyebrow">The person</span>
            <h2 style="margin-top:1rem;">
              More than a <span class="it">developer.</span>
            </h2>
            <p style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
              Outside the editor I travel — slowly, when I can. I read across genres
              (high fantasy on Sundays, Buffett's letters on Mondays). I treat investing
              as a long game and the gym as my daily reset. The thread that ties it all
              together is the same thing I look for in code: a pursuit of compounding
              returns.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section interests">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Off the clock</span>
        <h2>The four pillars <span class="serif" style="font-style:italic;color:var(--color-gold);">that keep me sharp.</span></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="interests-grid">
        <div class="lux-card interest reveal" style="--reveal-delay:60ms;position:relative;">
          <span class="num">— 01</span>
          <div class="ic">✈</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Travel</h3>
            <p class="body">Explorer of the world — from canal cities to mountain villages, I collect places the way some collect books.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lux-card interest reveal" style="--reveal-delay:140ms;position:relative;">
          <span class="num">— 02</span>
          <div class="ic">◈</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Investing</h3>
            <p class="body">Equities, FIIs, ETFs and Fixed Income — patiently building my own path to financial freedom.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lux-card interest reveal" style="--reveal-delay:220ms;position:relative;">
          <span class="num">— 03</span>
          <div class="ic">❦</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Reading</h3>
            <p class="body">From fantasy to finance — always learning, always taking notes in the margins.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lux-card interest reveal" style="--reveal-delay:300ms;position:relative;">
          <span class="num">— 04</span>
          <div class="ic">⟁</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Fitness</h3>
            <p class="body">The gym is my daily reset — discipline that quietly underwrites everything else.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="closing reveal">
        <div class="quote-mark">"</div>
        <div class="closing-text">
          The aim is simple — <span class="gold">freedom</span>.<br/>
          The means is patience, code, and compounding.
        </div>
        <div class="sig">— Long-term plan · Always shipping —</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
